3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed method involves training a neural network to predict story endings. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the proposed method involves the use of neural memory chains. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with narrative modeling, which could potentially involve audio storytelling.
